00:37.103 --> 00:38.686
[SIGHS]

01:03.028 --> 01:04.495
[GASPS]

01:04.497 --> 01:07.365
[♪♪♪]

01:10.770 --> 01:12.237
[CROWD SCREAMING]

01:23.716 --> 01:25.133
Ugh!
[HORN HONKS]

01:33.842 --> 01:37.195
[♪♪♪]

01:40.499 --> 01:42.867
This guy knows
where Jean is.

01:45.170 --> 01:47.922
[♪♪♪]

01:49.658 --> 01:51.742
[WHIMPERING]

01:54.163 --> 01:56.197
[GROWLING]

02:05.257 --> 02:06.474
[GRUNTS]

02:22.608 --> 02:23.541
[GROWLS]

02:31.450 --> 02:32.717
Oh, crud.

02:32.719 --> 02:35.486
Is that--
Is that Harpoon?

02:35.488 --> 02:38.439
Have you completely
lost it, Summers?

02:38.441 --> 02:40.341
I'm telling you,
he knows.

02:40.343 --> 02:42.226
Oh, so it's not enough

02:42.228 --> 02:44.662
you're ripping up the city
in broad daylight,

02:44.664 --> 02:46.864
you have to bring this nutjob
into our house?

02:46.866 --> 02:49.166
Maybe you've all forgotten
that Jean is missing,

02:49.168 --> 02:51.836
but I haven't.
STORM: Scott,

02:51.838 --> 02:53.371
it isn't like that.

02:53.373 --> 02:56.975
Emma, see what he knows.

03:01.079 --> 03:03.581
[POWERS BUZZ]

03:06.818 --> 03:09.270
He has no information
about Jean.

03:09.272 --> 03:11.772
What about Sinister?
Does he know where he is?

03:11.774 --> 03:13.825
I'm sorry.
Agh!

03:20.766 --> 03:22.000
Go.

03:23.835 --> 03:25.102
[SIGHS]

03:25.104 --> 03:26.620
Who exactly is
Sinister?

03:26.622 --> 03:28.272
He's a mutant scientist

03:28.274 --> 03:30.491
who collects genetic samples
of other mutants,

03:30.493 --> 03:32.410
usually by force.

03:32.412 --> 03:34.145
How charming.

03:34.147 --> 03:36.364
And why did your Mr. Sinister
want to do this?

03:36.366 --> 03:39.300
Supposedly to create
the ultimate mutant.

03:39.302 --> 03:40.752
And years ago
he was intent

03:40.754 --> 03:43.420
on using Jean Grey
in his experiments,

03:43.422 --> 03:45.006
but we stopped him.

03:45.008 --> 03:46.591
[HARPOON GROANS]
[CRACKLING]

03:48.594 --> 03:51.562
Sorry, he was
starting to wake up.

03:51.564 --> 03:53.531
Well, he can't stay here.

03:53.533 --> 03:56.167
Time for a drop and dash
in front of the M.R.D.

03:56.169 --> 03:58.769
[♪♪♪]

04:19.858 --> 04:21.526
What do you think
you're doing?

04:21.528 --> 04:23.727
If one of Sinister's
Marauders crawled out

04:23.729 --> 04:26.531
from under his rock,
then maybe others did too.

04:26.533 --> 04:28.766
This could be our only
chance to find Jean.

04:28.768 --> 04:30.768
Forget it, Summers.
What?

04:30.770 --> 04:32.403
It's the wrong play

04:32.405 --> 04:34.605
on a slim-to-none chance
he's got her.

04:34.607 --> 04:37.207
You shake down Sinister,
you'll start a war.

04:37.209 --> 04:40.411
Yeah? Well, you've gone
to war for far less.

04:40.413 --> 04:44.148
Maybe, but I'd never drag
the X-Men down with me.

04:44.150 --> 04:46.751
Fine, forget the X-Men.

04:46.753 --> 04:48.569
I'll do it alone.

05:03.935 --> 05:05.870
Scott.

05:05.872 --> 05:08.422
I can help you.

05:08.424 --> 05:11.359
Sorry, just got
the one helmet.

05:11.361 --> 05:13.711
Harpoon was on his way
to see someone

05:13.713 --> 05:16.347
called Blockbuster.
Yeah?

05:16.349 --> 05:19.150
Together they were to meet with
one of Sinister's generals.

05:19.152 --> 05:20.417
Arclight.

05:20.419 --> 05:23.487
The next rung up the ladder
might know where Sinister is.

05:23.489 --> 05:25.156
Why didn't you
tell me this before?

05:25.158 --> 05:28.459
I knew how Logan
would react.

05:28.461 --> 05:31.779
Besides, sometimes you have
to follow your heart.

05:32.814 --> 05:34.032
Thanks.

05:35.300 --> 05:38.803
[♪♪♪]

05:38.805 --> 05:41.472
So where is this meeting
supposed to take place?

05:41.474 --> 05:43.274
[PANTING]

05:48.163 --> 05:50.064
[GROWLING]

05:54.353 --> 05:57.671
It's all in the interest
of science, little Morlock.

05:57.673 --> 05:59.323
[GASPS]

05:59.325 --> 06:01.559
So at least take
comfort in that.

06:04.697 --> 06:07.098
Now, come peacefully.

06:26.718 --> 06:28.503
[♪♪♪]

06:32.091 --> 06:33.941
Get out of here, kid.

06:36.545 --> 06:38.429
X-Man.

06:38.431 --> 06:39.697
[GRUNTS]

06:41.717 --> 06:43.033
Aargh!

06:45.437 --> 06:48.055
Where is he?
Where is Sinister?

06:59.517 --> 07:01.251
Then let's do this.

07:03.972 --> 07:06.324
[CROWD SHOUTING]

07:17.937 --> 07:19.571
[BRAKES SCREECH]

07:20.822 --> 07:21.872
[GRUNTING]

07:27.095 --> 07:28.712
[HORN HONKING]

07:33.218 --> 07:35.553
[GRUNTING]

07:37.155 --> 07:39.757
Where is Sinister?

07:42.310 --> 07:43.711
[GROANS]

07:48.199 --> 07:50.602
[CROWD MOANING]

07:51.837 --> 07:52.820
Never mind.

08:12.357 --> 08:14.525
Arclight.
You're late.

08:14.527 --> 08:17.011
Take the samples that
Blockbuster and Harpoon gathered

08:17.013 --> 08:18.379
and bring them--
No.

08:18.381 --> 08:21.649
You have to listen.
Harpoon never made the drop,

08:21.651 --> 08:23.801
and Blockbuster
and I were attacked

08:23.803 --> 08:26.404
by Cyclops.

08:26.406 --> 08:28.439
I got away, but Blockbuster--

08:28.441 --> 08:30.792
You were attacked
by an X-Man

08:30.794 --> 08:32.777
and you came here?

08:34.361 --> 08:36.130
Connect me
to Sinister.

08:39.551 --> 08:41.568
[GRUNTS]

08:43.738 --> 08:46.291
We have a problem.

08:50.062 --> 08:52.764
[♪♪♪]

08:58.436 --> 09:00.337
What have you
done with Jean?

09:02.607 --> 09:04.108
Vertigo!

09:11.583 --> 09:14.402
Oh, she is so fired.

09:27.065 --> 09:28.850
What is happening
to my lab?

09:28.852 --> 09:30.367
<i>It's Cyclops.</i>

09:30.369 --> 09:33.370
<i>He's destroying everything.</i>
<i>There's nothing I can do.</i>

09:33.372 --> 09:36.424
<i>It's all gone.</i>
You are responsible.

09:39.177 --> 09:41.178
<i>What have you</i>
<i>done with Jean?</i>

09:41.180 --> 09:43.481
<i>Tell me!</i>
Arclight,

09:43.483 --> 09:47.184
listen to me very carefully.

09:47.186 --> 09:49.703
[♪♪♪]

09:49.705 --> 09:51.055
Aagh!

10:06.705 --> 10:09.173
LOGAN:
Ugh. You did what?

10:09.175 --> 10:11.692
I'm sorry, what was
the question?

10:11.694 --> 10:15.079
I couldn't understand you
with all the snarling.

10:15.081 --> 10:17.915
Don't play games
with me, Frost.

10:17.917 --> 10:20.017
He asked
for my help, Logan,

10:20.019 --> 10:22.720
much like you yourself did
not so long ago.

10:22.722 --> 10:25.523
Difference is Summers
ain't gonna survive

10:25.525 --> 10:27.457
a clash with Sinister.

10:27.459 --> 10:29.293
Scott can handle himself.

10:29.295 --> 10:31.128
He's a boy scout.

10:31.130 --> 10:33.264
He's not ready
for this kind of fight.

10:33.266 --> 10:36.049
You don't know Scott
any more than you do yourself.

10:37.603 --> 10:39.052
Perhaps your real concern

10:39.054 --> 10:41.121
is that you've made
the wrong decision.

10:41.123 --> 10:43.641
Again.
Frost!

10:43.643 --> 10:45.643
You should've
supported him,

10:45.645 --> 10:48.612
because what if he's right?
He ain't.

10:48.614 --> 10:51.616
Either way, you've
lost another X-Man,

10:51.618 --> 10:54.135
and you can't
blame that on me.

10:54.137 --> 10:55.987
Pack what you need.

10:55.989 --> 10:58.906
We're bringing
him back.

10:58.908 --> 11:00.908
Oh, and by the way,

11:00.910 --> 11:03.410
he borrowed your bike.
[GROWLS]

11:03.412 --> 11:06.063
[♪♪♪]

11:06.065 --> 11:08.048
[CARS HONKING]

11:38.630 --> 11:40.864
[GRUNTS]

12:21.156 --> 12:24.975
I-I didn't want to take her.
Sinister made us do it.

12:24.977 --> 12:26.393
Jean?

12:26.395 --> 12:28.095
I can tell you
where she is.

12:28.097 --> 12:30.380
Just don't hurt me.

12:35.253 --> 12:36.971
[CRASHING]

12:36.973 --> 12:39.657
Hey! Uh...

12:42.160 --> 12:44.028
KITTY:
And don't give him
to Magneto.

12:52.103 --> 12:54.739
[GROANING]

12:54.741 --> 12:57.174
LOGAN:
Well, I guess
hunting these slimeballs

12:57.176 --> 12:59.277
is one way to deal
with all that pent-up rage.

12:59.279 --> 13:02.496
He has every right
to be angry.

13:02.498 --> 13:04.431
Scott is a good person
in a world

13:04.433 --> 13:07.384
that exists solely
to crush good people.

13:07.386 --> 13:08.903
Why do you care, Frost?

13:08.905 --> 13:11.688
About Summers?
About any of this?

13:11.690 --> 13:13.223
It's not that I--

13:13.225 --> 13:16.443
Scott! He's--

13:16.445 --> 13:18.629
We have to go.
What did you see?

13:18.631 --> 13:20.764
He's being lead
into a trap.

13:20.766 --> 13:22.733
[♪♪♪]

13:25.670 --> 13:29.222
Sinister!

13:40.918 --> 13:42.820
Give her to me! Now!

13:42.822 --> 13:44.855
[LAUGHS]

13:44.857 --> 13:47.457
Xavier's prize student,

13:47.459 --> 13:49.310
the teacher's pet.

13:49.312 --> 13:51.095
If only he could
see you now,

13:51.097 --> 13:55.015
so angry,
so unwilling to think.

13:55.017 --> 13:57.368
You dare come after me?

13:57.370 --> 13:58.802
As if Sinister
was the name

13:58.804 --> 14:01.405
of a common thug
you could intimidate?

14:01.407 --> 14:05.759
Well, your days as a nuisance
to me are over.

14:08.780 --> 14:11.482
You wanna hit someone?
How about me?

14:22.327 --> 14:24.578
[♪♪♪]

14:27.465 --> 14:29.066
Aagh!

14:34.623 --> 14:37.157
[GRUNTING]

14:37.159 --> 14:39.110
Very impressive.

14:39.112 --> 14:41.845
As always, you never
fail to entertain.

14:41.847 --> 14:45.416
But you're smart enough to know
that you've already lost.

15:02.867 --> 15:05.069
Give me Jean
and I walk away.

15:05.071 --> 15:07.371
You are in no position
to bargain.

15:07.373 --> 15:10.357
The damage you caused tonight,
the lost genetic material,

15:10.359 --> 15:11.875
the sheer aggravation...

15:11.877 --> 15:14.945
Just-- Just give me Jean.

15:14.947 --> 15:16.446
That's all I want.

15:16.448 --> 15:20.250
I don't have Jean Grey.

15:20.252 --> 15:21.802
But-- But Arclight--

15:21.804 --> 15:25.122
That confession was to lure
you here.

15:25.124 --> 15:27.324
No.

15:27.326 --> 15:29.192
Madrox, restrain him.

15:29.194 --> 15:32.997
[SCREAMS]

15:41.773 --> 15:44.024
[ALL GRUNTING]

16:07.598 --> 16:10.033
[♪♪♪]

16:23.298 --> 16:24.915
Look at it this way:

16:24.917 --> 16:27.184
It's possible
you might finally

16:27.186 --> 16:29.220
be reunited with Jean,

16:29.222 --> 16:31.388
in the afterlife.

16:31.390 --> 16:35.559
But at least your DNA
will live on in this world.

16:35.561 --> 16:38.228
[LAUGHS]

16:38.230 --> 16:40.748
[♪♪♪]

16:50.591 --> 16:51.825
[GROWLS]

17:00.485 --> 17:02.252
Wow, there's a lot
of you.

17:35.920 --> 17:38.021
How infantile.

17:38.023 --> 17:39.422
Aaarrgh!

17:55.406 --> 17:57.240
Scott!
Scott, wait.

18:02.663 --> 18:04.882
[GRUNTING]

18:17.528 --> 18:19.462
LOGAN:
Cripes.

18:19.464 --> 18:22.599
Iceman, finish this!
Awesome!

18:38.150 --> 18:39.816
Sinister didn't have her.

18:39.818 --> 18:42.252
She's out there
somewhere.

18:42.254 --> 18:44.188
I can't stop.
I have to keep looking.

18:44.190 --> 18:45.589
I have to--

18:45.591 --> 18:48.158
Summers.

18:50.061 --> 18:53.430
Scott? Scott?

18:56.484 --> 18:58.135
How are you feeling?

18:58.137 --> 18:59.770
Not good.

19:01.473 --> 19:03.073
You had us worried.

19:03.075 --> 19:04.758
I'm sorry.

19:04.760 --> 19:06.476
I just--

19:06.478 --> 19:08.628
The thought of Jean
in Sinister's labs,

19:08.630 --> 19:11.114
it was too much.
I wasn't thinking.

19:11.116 --> 19:14.418
Yeah, you not thinking
took out every one of his goons.

19:14.420 --> 19:15.702
Next time
you stop thinking,

19:15.704 --> 19:17.605
point your head
at the Brotherhood.

19:17.607 --> 19:19.340
Ow!

19:19.342 --> 19:21.324
You came after me,

19:21.326 --> 19:23.426
even after the way
I've been acting.

19:23.428 --> 19:25.546
You'd have done the same
for any of us.

19:25.548 --> 19:27.731
Scott,
we'll find Jean

19:27.733 --> 19:29.583
but we'll do it
together.

19:29.585 --> 19:31.017
Now get some rest.

19:31.019 --> 19:32.602
Thanks.

19:39.710 --> 19:42.662
That just warms
the heart, don't it?

19:42.664 --> 19:45.215
Sure, I'm glad
you're alive and all,

19:45.217 --> 19:48.218
but you and me,
we've got a problem.

19:48.220 --> 19:50.637
You've got a choice
to make, Summers.

19:50.639 --> 19:52.690
Be an X-Man or don't,

19:52.692 --> 19:55.575
'cause this garbage
ain't gonna fly with me.

19:55.577 --> 19:59.129
You wanna go chase ghosts,
fine.

19:59.131 --> 20:01.715
But if you're gonna be here,
be here.

20:01.717 --> 20:04.501
Xavier wouldn't
kick you out,

20:04.503 --> 20:07.237
but don't think
for a second I won't.

20:07.239 --> 20:09.172
She's out there.
I know it.

20:09.174 --> 20:12.342
Then go look for her,
on your own.

20:12.344 --> 20:15.112
Because you're either one
of the team or you're gone.

20:15.114 --> 20:16.680
Now, which is it?

20:16.682 --> 20:18.649
[♪♪♪]

20:18.651 --> 20:20.450
I'll stay.

20:20.452 --> 20:21.936
What's that?

20:21.938 --> 20:25.172
It's over.
I'm staying here.

20:26.308 --> 20:27.974
Good.

20:39.186 --> 20:41.938
[WOMAN GASPS]

20:41.940 --> 20:44.308
Doctor. Doctor!

20:44.310 --> 20:45.959
Look, she's awake.

20:45.961 --> 20:48.678
Miss? Hello?

20:48.680 --> 20:50.581
How are you feeling?

20:50.583 --> 20:52.515
I'm tired,

20:52.517 --> 20:54.417
but I feel all right.

20:54.419 --> 20:56.686
Good. Can you
tell us your name?

20:56.688 --> 20:59.273
I--

20:59.275 --> 21:00.690
I don't know.

21:00.692 --> 21:02.625
I can't remember.

21:04.162 --> 21:06.563
[♪♪♪]

